National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan met with National Security Council Secretary Armen Grigoryan of Armenia to express the United States' commitment to peace, security, and prosperity in Armenia and the South Caucasus region. Sullivan expressed concern over ongoing tensions between Armenia and Azerbaijan, particularly military movements near un-demarcated borders, which he deemed irresponsible and provocative. He also welcomed the ongoing communication between the two sides and emphasized the U.S.' commitment to supporting confidence-building measures and regional reconciliation. Sullivan further appreciated the announcement that Turkey and Armenia will appoint special envoys to discuss the normalization process. Lastly, he expressed appreciation for Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan's participation in The Summit for Democracy and highlighted the strong cooperation between the U.S. and Armenia on reform, democratic institution-building, and economic development.